Exercise Step: Reach towards the square on the wall.
Once you touch the square, trace the wall down to the triangle.
Next, touch the circle on the wall.
From the circle, trace down towards the star on the wall. This should make an X along the wall.
Rest your arm by your side and shake it out if it starts to feel heavy or sore.
Change the direction of your arm movement from star to circle and triangle to square.
Repeat the exercise two more times.
Let your arm rest by your side after completing the exercise.
Pain Detection: pain when I reached the square
